<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870609-0092 </DOCNO><HL> Corrections andamp; Amplifications:Leonard Garment</HL><DD> 06/09/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LATAM MDESTMONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)AEROSPACE (ARO)EXECUTIVE (EXE)CONGRESS (CNG) </IN><TEXT>   LEONARD GARMENT, the lawyer of former White House National Security Adviser Robert McFarlane, didn't contend that Lawrence Walsh, the independent counsel in the Iran-Contra affair, was abusing his authority by pressing an overly broad investigation. In an earlier edition, Mr. Garment's comments were misrepresented.    (See: &quot;Walsh's Broad Stroke Approach in Investigation of Iran-Contra Affair Jars Legal Establishment&quot; -- WSJ June 8, 1987) </TEXT></DOC>